Job Description
Our Client are a leading global engineering and construction contractor and power equipment supplier delivering technically advanced, reliable facilities and equipment. They design and construct leading-edge processing facilities for the upstream oil and gas, gas monetization, LNG/GTL, refining, chemicals and petrochemicals, power, mining and metals, environmental, pharmaceuticals, biotechnology and healthcare industries.
Responsibilities:
Selection, preparation of material requisitions, technical specifications, technical evaluation of bids and review of vendor drawings/documents, construction & commissioning of LNG Tankage
Should be well conversant particularly on:
1.
Double & Full containment design
2.
Cryogenic material of construction
3.
EN 14620 & EN 1473 for Tank & Plant design & Construction
4.
Testing & Inspection requirements
5.
Contractor selection
6.
Construction & Safety procedures
Selection, preparation of material requisitions, technical specifications, technical evaluation of bids and review of vendor drawings/documents of static equipment such as Vessels, Reactors, Columns and Heat Exchangers
Qualifications:
Degree in Mechanical Engineering with at least 15 years of experience in LNG/Refinery / Petrochemical Projects with about 5 years in a lead position
Knowledge of design software such as PVELITE, COMPRESS, BJAC, TANK etc. is essential
Conversant with international codes and practices
Working experience in Design & Engineering team for Conceptual Studies, FEED, and EPC phases of grass-root and revamp projects
